Text: Migrated Calendar InformationThe attached file is a copy of your migrated calendar information If you imported your calendar automatically when you first logged on you do not need to continue Verify that your calendar information was imported correctly and then delete this message If you migrated calendar information to a personal folder file pst or were not prompted to import your calendar information automatically you can import it now by performing the following steps depending on your client platform Microsoft Outlook for Windows NT and Windows In Microsoft Outlook from the File menu choose Save Attachments Type the location and file name for the attached file and then choose Save From the File menu choose Import and Export Choose Import from another program or file and then choose Next If the file attachment is a cal file choose Schedule If the file attachment is an scd file choose Schedule If the file attachment is an sc file choose Schedule Plus Interchange Type the path and file name of the file you want to import Under Options select Do not import duplicate items to ensure that any previously imported items will not be duplicated Type the password for the calendar file and then choose OK Choose Finish to complete the calendar migration Microsoft Outlook Calendar for Windows for Workgroups Version and Windows Version If you migrated calendar information to the Microsoft Exchange Server information store your calendar is automatically migrated and you do not need to continue Verify that your calendar information was imported correctly and then delete this message If you migrated calendar information to a personal folder file pst or your calendar information was not imported correctly you can import it now by performing the following steps depending on your client platform On the calendar message from the File menu choose Save As Choose Attachments type the location and file name and then choose OK If the file you need to import is already a Schedule Plus Interchange sc file go to step If the file you need to import is a Schedule cal file or a Schedule scd file start Microsoft Outlook Calendar by selecting the Show Calendar toolbar button in Microsoft Outlook or running Microsoft Outlook Calendar from the group where it is installed From the main Microsoft Outlook Calendar menu choose File and then choose Open Then choose Archive or Project Schedule Select the file to be opened by typing the path and file name that you specified in step and then choose OK In this new Microsoft Outlook Calendar window select File and then choose Export Then choose Outlook Calendar Interchange Select a location and file name for the export file sc and then choose OK Close the Outlook Calendar window From the main Microsoft Outlook Calendar menu select File and Import Then choose Outlook Calendar Interchange Select the file to be imported by typing the path to the sc file and then choose OK The calendar data from the sc file will be imported to your Microsoft Outlook Calendar
